{
  "stem": "10478.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 115,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The, the curfew, of course, was one of the laws.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 115,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] there was a whole bunch of new, new laws you had to, to, to try to-- and we were-- we had to hand in our radios, you know.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 115,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We're not allowed to listen to the broadcasts from either England or America.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 115,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we only listen-- were allowed to listen to the German broadcast.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 116,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they were afraid we were going to read-- going to hear the truth of what was really going to happen.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 116,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we were only just allowed to listen to German propaganda.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 117,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's what they did, yeah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not, not right away, but later on, when we all were required to have an ID card with a picture and a fingerprint on that, then they put on the ID cards, with the Jewish, a black J.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So anytime they was  in control, they could, right away, see that man is a Jew.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then, of course, they picked up some Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was something around sabotage or whatever they are.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's the Jews' act.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 118,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then they picked up some Jewish men in, in, in Maastricht or in other places, and sent them to camp, yeah.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 119,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember one case, one man was, for a reason, arrested by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 119,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was-- they brought him a  transport to Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 119,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I knew his wife.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 119,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she was still at  home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 119,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She wasn't-- it was non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 119,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she asked me to, to go along with her in the train.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 119,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so  she talked to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 119,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I talked to her.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 119,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And what we said was meant for him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 119,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was sitting in some-- somewhere in the same area with some soldiers who were transferred into Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 120,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, never.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 121,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Never.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 122,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, one particular friend, by the name Van Assen, V-A-N A-S-S-E-N.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 122,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was arrested, and he had the two Jewish persons in his home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 122,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were arrested as well.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 123,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They all went-- sent to a camp, and they never came back.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 124,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The majority did, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 124,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For example, we were not allowed to have a radio.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 124,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have a clandestine radio.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 124,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we listened to the-- to the British broadcast to hear what was going on in the war, you know, and--",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 125,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was done secretly, yeah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 126,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had that hidden somewhere in the-- in the floor.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 126,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at night, we took it out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 126,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then we listened to the BBC.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 127,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not at that time.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 127,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Later on, of course, and then I was aware of that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 128,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By the Germans, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 128,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When you informed for the Germans, they, they, they got, of course, their salary and benefits.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 129,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 130,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's right, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 131,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Only, in my, my particular case, it was, [? do you know, ?] a couple of-- three guys, [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH], and another guy did, Theo [NON-ENGLISH], who were informers for the German, yeah.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 132,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 133,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
